    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-02T21:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-02T21:40:00-05:00" n="281"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d281">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1134.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Sullivan</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-02T22:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 2, 1914, 10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Provisional Government has requested me to transmit following message: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>President Bordas respectfully begs to inform President Wilson that
                            fighting began yesterday between the Government forces and those of
                            General Arias who is resisting substitution of governors hostile to the
                            smuggling interests in lieu of Arias governors. My Government can
                            control the situation if it can obtain the necessary funds. Otherwise
                            state of anarchy likely to ensue. I appeal to the high sense of justice
                            of the American Government to consider our situation.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Provisional Government is about to ask Congress to suspend constitutional
                    guaranties but believe Congress will refuse.</p>
                <p>Bordas leaves here to-morrow with troops to take the field in person against
                    Arias rebellion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
